commit.message: Allow URI of web service to be set on the Guzzle implementations of \Josser\Client\Transport\TransportInterface as alternative of relying on the base_uri of the Guzzle client.
Make sure to read whole response stream, not just the remainder from current stream pointer

full list of changes below:
- removed bitcoin client
- refactored http transport
- enhanced travis setup

full list of changes below:

- update composer.json
- updated composer.lock
- updated documentation
- changed license from BSD to MIT
make static Client::send and instance method and allow runtime switching of transport and protocol.
fixed outdated link to JSON-RPC 2.0 specification
added few more tests and fixed request validation

full list of changes below:
* added JSON-RPC 2.0 tests
* fixed JSON-RPC 2.0 request and response validation
* fixed JSON-RPC 1.0 response validation
fixed transforming request object into DTO

full list of changes below:
* added more tests
* fixed JSON-RPC 1.0 request validation
* changed JsonRpc1Test::testGenerateRequestId as it was lame

full list of changes below:
* simplified data providers and removed unused ones
* make tests more explicit

full list of changes below:
* added more tests and improved existing ones
* request/response DTO validation is now hidden

full list of changes below:
* simplified phpunit configuration file
* colorize phpunit output

Full list of changes below:
* leverage Symfony serializer component
* distinguish client protocol interface
* removed @covers annotation in test files as xdebug knows it better
* [fix] excluded tests/ and vendor/ from under code coverage report
refactored out http transport factory method

Full list of changes below:

* made protocol required by client object
* simplified RequestInterface
* simplified ProtocolInterface
* decoupled Request and Notification
* added some methods signature and phpDoc fixes
* allowed to send requests without using whole client object
* InvalidArgumentException become InvalidRequestException
* removed unused BadMethodCallException
* adjusted tests
phpDoc and some methods signature fixes
allow to use custom request id with plain client calls
Either error or message must be null in response object. Not both and not neither. [json-rpc 1.0]
response object must specify both "message" and "error" [json-rpc 1.0]
after some consideration I came to conclusion that having 0.005 BTC does not mean being broke :)
tests should be placed under Josser\Tests namespace
add shortcut / factory method for creating bitcoin client with http transport
add more details about error handling

issue_comments.body: Thanks, nice to know someone is using it :)

@dennisverspuij  I made some [cleanup](https://github.com/alanbem/Josser/pull/4) on `master` so now travis would not fail for your PRs. Can you rebase them please?

After that I will merge them and release version `0.3.0`
